column11: ['school for visual storytelling', 'jobs for artists', 'career paths for artists', 'business tips for artists', 'how to make money as an artist', 'income streams for artists', 'career advice for artists', "artists don't starve", 'school of visual storytelling']
column12:
BIG thank you to the School of Visual Storytelling for sponsoring this video! http://svslearn.com/kelseyrodriguez. Artists don't need to starve, and I'm tired of people saying that modern artists "have" to become influencers in order to make a living. 

There are a TON of options out there for creative people. From becoming a textile designer, an in-house illustrator for a small company, or a prop artist/designer for an indie-production studio, there are OPTIONS out there for you. 

Just as an aside-- while I do mention movie poster work in this video, please respect the ongoing SAG-AFTRA and GWA strike by actors and writers, who are striking against major studios and seeking better pay and working conditions. They've asked content creators to refrain from promoting (even organically) stricken work.

column12:
We NEED to talk about the decline of Twitter. Thank you to Squarespace for sponsoring this video: https://squarespace.com/kelseyrodriguez

So, Threads launched last week. While I'm pretty sad about Twitter's painful and prolonged death (because let's be real, how can they come back from this?? there are new scandals EVERY WEEK) I'm also really conflicted about Thread's existence, and it's parent company: Meta. 

Twitter has been going downhill ever since Elon Musk purchased it last year, and the vibrant artistic community that used to live there is increasingly moving off-platform. So where are artists supposed to go next? Is Threads the next social media platform for artists and creative content creators? Let's talk about it.

column2: How to Download Youtube Videos on iPhone in 2023
column4: How to Sell Digital Products & Downloads
column12:
Did you ever want to download your Youtube videos in HD but you're only using the free version? No worries, let me show you how to download Youtube videos on iPhone in 2023!

Let's begin by opening the "Youtube" app.
Next, tap on your profile icon at the top-right corner of the screen, then click "Settings". Select the "Offline" button.
Lastly, tap the "Download quality" and set your desired resolution, Let's set it to "10-80 p, Full HD".
Now go to the youtube video that you want to download, press the 3 dot icon at the bottom part of the youtube video. Tap on "Download video" once downloading is done, you can now watch your youtube video in HD offline!

Give it a thumbs up and don't forget to follow if you find this video helpful!

#youtube #download #tipsandtricks #tutorial

column12:
How to make money online and earn $60,000 a year selling one product with no inventory. This seller on Etsy is doing it. And here's how you're gonna do it too. Start by going to ChatGPT, create your free account and ask for funny sayings to put on a mug. Then make a canva account. Find the mug template and select Blank. Type out your design. They have tons of free fonts to choose from. Link your design to Print by making a free account. Then list your product on Etsy. When an order is placed, Printful will be notified and they will create and ship your product to the customer. This mug has been purchased over 4000 times at a selling price of 1529. This mug has made this seller $66,802 and that is how you can make money online and earn $60,000 a year selling one product with no inventory. Start hustling!

column11: ['content creator', 'content creation', 'how to become a content creator', 'Content creator tips', 'content creator inspiration', 'content creator hacks', 'influencer tips', 'influencer hacks', 'become a content creator full time', 'become and influencer full time', 'how to be a content creator', 'grow as a content creator', 'grow your following', 'become an influencer']
column12:
‚ÄúWhat if my family and friends think it‚Äôs dumb pursuing a job on social media‚Ä¶?‚Äù

‚ÄúWhat if I try but fail...? It‚Äôs probably easier to just play it safe and stick with what I know.‚Äù¬†

If you‚Äôre having these thoughts, you're not alone. I've been there, and I'm sure a lot of us have too. But I want to encourage you, don‚Äôt be the one to tell yourself no.

You have big dreams for a reason. You get to pursue them regardless of what others think or say.¬†

There‚Äôs no point in waiting around for the ‚Äòperfect time‚Äô (because, trust me, a "perfect time" doesn‚Äôt exist!).¬†

When I first started pursuing my dream of being a full-time content creator...I put off for a longggg time because I constantly told myself‚Ä¶¬†

‚ÄúI‚Äôm just too busy right now.‚Äù "I'm waiting for a sign." "You have no idea what you're doing, it's going to be too hard"

Wanna know what changed? Nope, I didn't walk outside a see a plane flying by with a sign in the back saying "go chase your dreams, you're ready". And my calendar never really changed - but my priorities did.¬†

I just chose to make my ideas and dreams a priority in my life. I chose to give them space on my calendar.¬†

I want you to do the same. Join me next week LIVE while I teach you how to plan out your content calendar for the rest of the year. 

Will you choose to make space for your dreams? What if it turns out better than you imagined üß°

Click the link in the comment below to save your seat, because if you've been "waiting for a sign" like I was, consider this it!

If you are considering deleting your Shopify store, it is important to understand the consequences and steps involved in the process. Deleting your store will permanently remove all of your data, including products, customers, orders, and settings. Before proceeding with the deletion, ensure that you have all the necessary information and backups of your data. 

To delete your Shopify store, go to the settings page and click on the "Account" tab. Scroll down to the "Store status" section and click on "Close store." Follow the prompts to confirm the deletion, and your store will be permanently removed from Shopify. Remember, once deleted, your store cannot be recovered.

Adding variants in Shopify is crucial for any business owner looking to offer various options to their customers. To add variants in Shopify in 2023, simply navigate to the product in question and click on the "Variants" tab. From there, click on "Add Variant" and input the necessary information, such as the variant's color, size, or material.

column2: Is Velocity Banking Strategy a SCAM? - Expert Proves It Doesn't Work
column11: ['velocity banking', 'velocity banking strategy', 'velocity banking explained', 'pay down debt faster', 'pay off your debt faster', 'debt snowball', 'debt snowball method', 'debt avalanche', 'debt avalanche method', 'personal finance', 'debt consolidation', 'william lee', 'think wealthy velocity banking', 'dave ramsey', 'suze orman', 'vanntastic!', 'vanntastic velocity banking', 'vanntastic finance', 'velocity channel']
column12:
Velocity Banking Strategy is supposedly a way to pay down debt faster by doing debt consolidation using a revolving credit line like a Home Equity Line of Credit (HELOC) or a credit card. However, in many cases, the Velocity Banking strategy doesn't work. This video is velocity banking explained: I explain and demonstrate why using velocity banking could take longer to pay off your debt and cost you more in interest expenses. Velocity banking almost certainly will not work to pay down debt faster when you are using a higher interest rate revolving loan to pay down a lower interest rate term loan. It might work if you can use a lower interest rate revolving loan to pay down higher interest rate term loan. However, it is less common for someone who is burdened by a high rate term loan to be able to get a lower rate revolving loan.... which is why I make the general statement that Velocity Banking Doesn't Work.  This is an important topic in personal finance. Watch the video to see the actual math for several scenarios. People interested in the debt snowball method and the debt avalanche method will find this useful, too. Check out some of the videos from Vanntastic finance, Velocity Channel, Suze Ormon and Dave Ramsey for other opinions on the topic. Some agree with me, some don't. I showed my math in full detail.

Your host in this video has been the CFO of several software companies and offers a lifetime of business experience to his audience. Will has an undergraduate degree in Economics, an MBA in finance from Cornell University, earned the CFA charter (Chartered Financial Analyst), and has worked as an equity research analyst at top Wall Street firms in addition to his experience running entrepreneurial companies.

Are you looking for inspiration on how to grow your business in a crowded market?

Look no further than Happilo, a premium gourmet brand for dry fruits and healthy snacking. Founded by Vikas D Nahar with just ‚Çπ10,000, Happilo has grown into a 500 crore revenue business, despite operating in a highly unorganized segment of the FMCG space.

In this video, we present to you Happilo‚Äôs business case study and explore how Vikas leveraged multiple pivots, creative ad campaigns, and a laser focus on brand equity to achieve success. We cover how he identified pain-points in the market, pivoted his product line to offer more variety and improved shelf-life, and entered the offline omnichannel space to build a strong retail and distribution network.

Happilo's branding strategy includes a mix of Above the Line (ATL) and Below the Line (BTL) activations. By partnering with Rajasthan Royals as a title sponsor for IPL, the brand positioned itself as a healthy alternative for guilt-free snacking for cricket fans. Happilo's Diwali campaign with Bollywood stars Sid Malhotra and Kiara Advani helped the brand tap into the movie-going audience and add XP points to the association factor in building brand equity.

By keeping brand equity at the core of their business, Happilo has been able to capture a 20% share in the organized Dry Fruits market in a short span of time. Will the brand achieve international status as a homegrown Dry Fruits brand? Will Happilo become synonymous with healthy snacking among young adults? Only time will tell.
